Nigeria to Protect Jobs Power Utilities’ Sale, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-03T08:45:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/nigeria-to-protect-jobs-power-utilities-sale-thisday-says.html
Nigerian workers in state-owned power
companies will keep their jobs after the utilities are sold,
 ThisDay  reported, citing presidential adviser Barth Nnaji.  Nigeria ,  Africa ’s most populous nation and top oil
producer, plans to sell six state-owned transmission and 11
thermal-generation companies by July, according to the power
ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 